 null, "comments": 7, "created_at": "2018-03-03T09:57:13Z", "updated_at": "2018-04-24T23:16:45Z", "closed_at": "2018-03-23T17:29:48Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/pulls/17396", "html_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/17396", "diff_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/17396.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/17396.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>This PR implements MKL repos for Mac (tested) and Windows (not tested yet)<br>\nAs well as reworks MKL.BUILD to support all 3 desktop platforms</p>\n<p><strong>Update 1</strong> Unfortunately, because of bazel bug <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"289965802\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/4480\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/4480/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/4480\">bazelbuild/bazel#4480</a> you will still experience loader issues on Mac and you will be forced to install MKL globally or deal with DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH to overcome invalid rpath in generated .so files of tensorflow (similar to <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"199435860\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/6729\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/6729/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/6729\">#6729</a> for CUDA libraries in dependencies).</p>\n<p><strong>Update 2</strong> Bazel 0.12.0 (not yet released) fixes the issue and it builds and runs flawlessly (verified with <a href=\"https://releases.bazel.build/0.12.0/rc1/index.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">0.12.0rc1</a> )</p>", "body_text": "This PR implements MKL repos for Mac (tested) and Windows (not tested yet)\nAs well as reworks MKL.BUILD to support all 3 desktop platforms\nUpdate 1 Unfortunately, because of bazel bug bazelbuild/bazel#4480 you will still experience loader issues on Mac and you will be forced to install MKL globally or deal with DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH to overcome invalid rpath in generated .so files of tensorflow (similar to #6729 for CUDA libraries in dependencies).\nUpdate 2 Bazel 0.12.0 (not yet released) fixes the issue and it builds and runs flawlessly (verified with 0.12.0rc1 )", "body": "This PR implements MKL repos for Mac (tested) and Windows (not tested yet)\r\nAs well as reworks MKL.BUILD to support all 3 desktop platforms\r\n\r\n**Update 1** Unfortunately, because of bazel bug https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/4480 you will still experience loader issues on Mac and you will be forced to install MKL globally or deal with DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH to overcome invalid rpath in generated .so files of tensorflow (similar to https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/6729 for CUDA libraries in dependencies).\r\n\r\n**Update 2** Bazel 0.12.0 (not yet released) fixes the issue and it builds and runs flawlessly (verified with [0.12.0rc1](https://releases.bazel.build/0.12.0/rc1/index.html) ) "}